com.biorecorder.edflib

Class HeaderConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.biorecorder.edflib.HeaderConfig

  • public class HeaderConfig
extends java.lang.Object
    Class (data-structure) that allows to store the information required to create EDF/BDF file header and correctly extract data from the DataRecords. It has the following fields (and their corresponding getters and setters):
    • patient identification
    • recording identification
    • recording recordingStartTime
    • number of data records
    • duration of a data record (in seconds)

    Configuration of every measuring channel is described by a separate special class SignalConfig, that store all important information about the channel: number of sample coming from that channel, its digital and physical minimum and maximum, physical dimension (uV or Ohm) and so on.

    HeaderConfig must contain a list of configurations for all measuring channels (signals) and we have to add them successively in the same order in which the samples belonging to the channels will be placed (saved) in DataRecords.

    To add the signal (channel) configuration use the method addSignalConfig(SignalConfig)

    To get the signal configuration ( ! the numbering starts at 0 ! ) - getSignalConfig(int)

    To get the number of the signals in data record - getNumberOfSignals()

    To get the number of bytes in header record - getNumberOfBytesInHeaderRecord()

    See Also:
    SignalConfig
